.TH "atc_alloc_descriptor" 9 "atc_alloc_descriptor" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
atc_alloc_descriptor \- allocate and return an initialized descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct at_desc *" atc_alloc_descriptor
.BI "(struct dma_chan *chan "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chan" 12
the channel to allocate descriptors for
.IP "gfp_flags" 12
GFP allocation flags
.SH "NOTE"
The ack-bit is positioned in the descriptor flag at creation time
to make initial allocation more convenient. This bit will be cleared
and control will be given to client at usage time (during
preparation functions).
